  "prompt": "I'm 23 years old and I have never been in love. How can you tell if you are in love? Is there a difference between loving a person and being in love?",
  "response": "Love is a complex emotion, and people experience it differently. Here are some signs that might indicate you're in love:\n\n1. Loving Someone vs. Being in Love:\n- Loving someone can be platonic (like family or friends)\n- Being in love typically involves romantic attraction and deeper emotional intimacy\n\nSigns of Being in Love:\n1. Strong emotional connection\n2. Wanting to share your life with that person\n3. Thinking about them frequently\n4. Prioritizing their happiness\n5. Feeling vulnerable and comfortable with them\n6. Physical and emotional attraction\n7. Wanting to be a better person for them\n8. Experiencing a mix of excitement and comfort\n9. Imagining a future together\n10. Accepting their flaws\n\nEmotional Indicators:\n- Butterflies in stomach\n- Increased heart rate when near them\n- Wanting to be close and connect\n- Feeling safe and secure\n- Willing to compromise\n- Deep empathy and understanding\n\nPractical Advice:\n- Don't rush love\n- Be open to experiences\n- Work on self-love and personal growth\n- Be patient with yourself\n- Keep an open mind\n\nRemember, love is unique for everyone. There's no universal \"right\" way to experience it.",
